data.description: This charming 3 story home is comprised of 2196 square feet. The home consist of 4 very large bedrooms able to accommodate king size bed and furniture, 2 full bathrooms and one half bath with laundry hookup. New hardwood flooring throughout, New stairs, newer kitchen with hardwood floors and stainless steel appliance along with New granite countertop. Dining room and living room has an open concept. Front den area can be expanded to create a grand foyer and reception area. Basement has new concrete walls and flooring. Home receives ample amounts of sunlight and has a skylight at the third floor level. The third floor host a master suite with walk in shower, a large soaking tub and double sink vanity. This home has gas heating with a Newer Crown heater and Newer hot water tank.  The outdoor space has new privacy fencing and a new concrete deck with excellent garden space for the urban farmer. This home is a real gem with lots of possibilities for additional enhancements. Just two blocks from Fairmount Ave and a block away from up and coming Ridge Ave. Centrally located to Philadelphia Met Theater, Center City, the Philadelphia Museum of Art, Barnes Museum, Temple University and the Rodin Museum.  There are several restaurants and cafes to choose from. The new Whole Foods complex is approximately half mile away. Philadelphia Sports Club, and Retro Fitness are just a few of several area gyms and yoga studios. Fairmount Park's Kelly Drive offers a scenic route for runners, bikers, walkers and everyone else. There is a Community Garden for all a few blocks away at Wallace and N19th. Individuals can sign up for your own garden plot. Access to public transportation is a snap in every direction.
